candidates.title: Make jni optional on android target and add a feature for it
candidates.body:
Hi there, this change allows slauth to be compiled to android target without jni for example, when using termux to run rust projects, jni is not needed because you won't interface with java at all.
I am afraid that this will break something that uses  slauth to be bundled in android applications, but to fix that, people would have to compile slauth with `features = ["android"]` so jni gets compiled together.

candidates.title: Remove strict versioning on wasm bindgen
candidates.body:
This allows projects to be compiled as long as they have the same major and minor versions, ignoring the patch number.
One example is, I was using iced which requires "0.2.69" but should accept anything that is >=0.2.69,<0.3 but it wouldn't compile my project because slauth had a strict requirement on 0.2.60.
I assume it **should** be safe to allow patches to be compiled against this version.
